---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="POCN — Case Study">

  <div class="section">
    <a class="breadcrumb" href="/Personal/case-studies/">← <span>Case Studies</span> / POCN</a>
    <div class="cs-hero" style="border:0;padding:0;overflow:hidden"><img src="/Personal/Images/POCN/pocn-cs-gfx-1.jpg" alt="POCN case study graphic" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;display:block" /></div>
    <div class="cs-tags"><span class="cs-tag">Performance</span><span class="cs-tag">Healthcare</span><span class="cs-tag">Programmatic</span><span class="cs-tag">HCP Marketing</span></div>
    <div class="cs-title">Driving Efficiency in Programmatic Media for Regulated Healthcare</div>
    <div class="cs-subtitle">Managed $1.7M+ in pharmaceutical media across 30+ concurrent HCP campaigns — driving compounding efficiency gains while consistently hitting contracted KPIs in a regulated environment.</div>
    <div class="cs-meta-card">
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Client</div><div class="cs-meta-value">POCN</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Duration</div><div class="cs-meta-value">May 2022 – Jul 2024 (26 months)</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Role</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Digital Marketing Manager</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Industry</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Healthcare / Pharma</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Clients</div><div class="cs-meta-value">J&amp;J · Lilly · AbbVie · Regeneron</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="stat-strip">
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">$1.7M+</div><div class="stat-label">Total media managed</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">30+</div><div class="stat-label">Concurrent campaigns at peak</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">50+</div><div class="stat-label">Pharmaceutical therapies supported</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Context · Action · Result</div>
    <div class="car-grid">
      <div class="car-sidebar">
        <div class="car-step active" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-pocn-1')"><div class="car-step-label">01 · Context</div><div class="car-step-title">The situation</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-pocn-2')"><div class="car-step-label">02 · Action</div><div class="car-step-title">What I did</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-pocn-3')"><div class="car-step-label">03 · Result</div><div class="car-step-title">What it produced</div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div id="car-pocn-1" class="car-content">
          <div class="car-content-label">01 · Context</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">A narrow clinical audience, fixed KPI benchmarks, and an MLR-gated creative pipeline.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">POCN connects pharmaceutical brands with Nurse Practitioner and Physician Assistant audiences. Campaigns spanned 50+ therapies for J&amp;J, Eli Lilly, AbbVie, and Regeneron. Every asset moved through MLR review before deployment, audience pools were small, and KPI targets were set by the client up front — so success wasn't about chasing growth, it was about delivering contracted metrics more efficiently each cycle.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-pocn-2" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">02 · Action</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Sole programmatic operator across 30+ concurrent campaigns, plus a full DSP migration.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Owned setup, pacing, and optimization across up to 30 concurrent campaigns spanning multiple therapeutic areas — segmenting NP and PA audiences for precision targeting and tightening spend continuously against fixed benchmarks. Mid-engagement, led the migration off a third-party DSP onto a proprietary internal platform, working between Product, Engineering, and the white-label vendor to surface real operator feedback and ship usability improvements.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-pocn-3" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">03 · Result</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">$1.7M+ managed, $200K+ in annual platform cost eliminated, KPIs held throughout.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Over 26 months, delivered consistent at-or-under-budget performance against contracted KPIs across the full portfolio. The DSP migration eliminated $200K+ in annual platform license costs with zero performance disruption, while improving operational control and campaign scalability. Performance gains came from improved targeting precision and continuous optimization — not increased spend.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Overview</div>
    <div class="car-content-body">POCN is a healthcare marketing platform connecting pharmaceutical brands with highly targeted Nurse Practitioner (NP) and Physician Assistant (PA) audiences. I led programmatic and paid media execution across a portfolio of pharmaceutical campaigns, operating within a tightly regulated environment where audience targeting, creative approvals, and campaign performance were all constrained by compliance requirements. Over a 26-month engagement, I managed media investment across multiple therapeutic areas — supporting campaigns for Johnson &amp; Johnson, Eli Lilly, AbbVie, and Regeneron.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">The challenge</div>
    <div class="car-content-body">
      <p style="margin:0 0 12px">Unlike traditional performance marketing, success in pharmaceutical media is not driven by aggressive KPI growth. Campaigns operate within fixed constraints:</p>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0">
        <li>Strict legal and MLR (Medical, Legal, Regulatory) approval processes</li>
        <li>Narrow, highly specific HCP audiences (NPs and PAs)</li>
        <li>Predefined KPI benchmarks set by pharmaceutical clients</li>
        <li>Limited flexibility in creative and messaging</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin:0">The challenge was not to continuously increase performance metrics — it was to deliver those metrics more efficiently over time.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">My role</div>
    <div class="car-content-body">
      <p style="margin:0 0 12px">I owned the execution and optimization of all programmatic and paid social campaigns, including:</p>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0">
        <li>Campaign setup and audience segmentation (NP / PA targeting)</li>
        <li>Budget allocation and pacing across concurrent campaigns</li>
        <li>Performance monitoring and optimization across channels</li>
        <li>Cross-functional collaboration with analytics, product, and sales teams</li>
        <li>Translating campaign data into actionable insights for clients</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin:0">At peak, I was managing 30+ concurrent campaigns simultaneously, each tied to different therapies, brands, and performance targets.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Approach</div>
    <div class="car-content-body">
      <p style="margin:0 0 14px">Instead of chasing KPI expansion, I focused on system-level efficiency improvements.</p>
      <div class="car-content-title" style="margin-bottom:6px">1. Optimization over expansion</div>
      <p style="margin:0 0 8px">Campaigns were continuously refined to:</p>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 14px 18px;padding:0">
        <li>Reduce wasted spend</li>
        <li>Improve audience targeting precision</li>
        <li>Identify and scale high-performing segments</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="car-content-title" style="margin-bottom:6px">2. Budget discipline</div>
      <p style="margin:0 0 8px">All campaigns were:</p>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 14px 18px;padding:0">
        <li>Carefully paced</li>
        <li>Adjusted dynamically based on performance signals</li>
        <li>Maintained at or below allocated budgets</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="car-content-title" style="margin-bottom:6px">3. Cross-channel alignment</div>
      <p style="margin:0">Performance insights from programmatic, LinkedIn, and Meta were used to refine strategy across all active campaigns.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Platform migration</div>
    <div class="car-content-body">
      <p style="margin:0 0 12px">Mid-engagement, I led the migration off a third-party DSP (Lasso / MediaOS) onto a proprietary internal platform — eliminating $200K+ in annual platform license costs while improving operational control and campaign scalability.</p>
      <p style="margin:0 0 8px">The migration required:</p>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 12px 18px;padding:0">
        <li>Testing workflows across all active campaigns before cutover</li>
        <li>Identifying inefficiencies in campaign execution and surfacing them to product</li>
        <li>Providing real-world operator feedback to the white-label vendor and internal engineering team to improve usability</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin:0">This was the strongest cross-functional work of the engagement — operating between Product, Engineering, and a vendor to ship improvements based on real campaign-operator feedback, with a quantifiable cost outcome.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Results</div>
    <div class="car-content-body">
      <p style="margin:0 0 14px">The outcome was not rapid KPI growth — it was consistent performance with increasing efficiency over time.</p>
      <div class="car-content-title" style="margin-bottom:6px">By the numbers</div>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 14px 18px;padding:0">
        <li>$1.7M+ in media managed</li>
        <li>30+ concurrent campaigns operated simultaneously</li>
        <li>50+ pharmaceutical therapies supported</li>
        <li>$200K+ annual platform cost eliminated through DSP migration</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="car-content-title" style="margin-bottom:6px">Operational outcomes</div>
      <ul style="margin:0 0 14px 18px;padding:0">
        <li>Consistent at-or-under-budget delivery across the 26-month engagement</li>
        <li>Reliable KPI achievement against contracted client targets</li>
        <li>Successful DSP migration with zero performance disruption</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin:0">Performance gains came from improved targeting precision, better budget allocation, and continuous optimization — not increased spend or inflated metrics.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Key insight</div>
    <div class="car-content-body">
      <p style="margin:0 0 12px">In regulated environments, success isn't defined by how high metrics climb — it's defined by how efficiently those metrics are achieved. Consistent KPI delivery while improving cost efficiency, within a highly constrained system, is the actual operator achievement.</p>
      <p style="margin:0">This work reflects the ability to operate at the intersection of performance marketing, product feedback loops, and regulated industry constraints — balancing scale, complexity, and efficiency to deliver reliable outcomes for pharmaceutical clients.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" style="border-bottom:none">
    <hr class="cs-rule" />
    <div class="next-prev">
      <a class="nav-card" href="/Personal/case-studies/scandalous/"><div class="nav-card-dir">← Previous</div><div class="nav-card-title">Scandalous — Brand system</div><div class="nav-card-tag">Brand · GTM</div></a>
      <a class="nav-card right" href="/Personal/case-studies/sigil/"><div class="nav-card-dir">Next →</div><div class="nav-card-title">SIGIL — GTM for original IP</div><div class="nav-card-tag">GTM · Brand</div></a>
    </div>
    <div class="btn-row"><a class="btn" href="/Personal/case-studies/">← All case studies</a></div>
  </div>

</Base>
